{
  "stem": "1581.4",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But that was-- nobody could give in to any bleeding or injury because we knew what would happen if you would give up or fall.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So we trundled away.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Whenever you had to go to the latrine, you had to ask permission, military fashion.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We who were in an army, we had it fairly easy.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But the other guys who had to learn all this rigmarole of standing in attention, and-- and loud, and yell loud out what you wanted.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "When you went to the latrine, if you lingered more than half a minute, you were hit over the head from the outside.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And so there was no way of resting there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And the-- the days were endless.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "You had to count every minute and every hour, and the clock didn't seem to go.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And there was this bitter cold, which was alleviated by the labor, because you-- you got quite warm through the labor, but there was always this gnawing, incredible hunger pain and the empty stomach.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And you saw how you became thinner and thinner.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And when the work was over, again we had to go into formation, march home, and again, we had to stand in appel.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "We were counted over and over again.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And finally, we were given this kind of a dirty water that they called soup.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And it was always a piece of luck when you were on line and the kettle came to the bottom because then you had the luck to get maybe a piece of potato or a leaf of cabbage in it.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Otherwise, you just had this hot, dirty water.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But at least it was something to get into your stomach.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And we gulped it down, and that was the end of the day.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
